The paper deals with landmark/pose estimation in computer vision, which is a core topic in computer vision and image processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel structure-aware fully convolutional network, which involves deep learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. The paper also incorporates priors about the structure of pose components, which involves artificial intelligence techniques, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely category. The paper also deals with geometric constraints of landmark point inter-connectivity, which involves computational geometry techniques, making cs.GR (Computer Graphics) another likely category. Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed approach on three pose-related tasks, which involves multimedia techniques, making cs.MM (Multimedia) another likely category.
